tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows elevated creatinine, suggesting impaired renal function, and mild metabolic acidosis (low COâ, high chloride). There is also mild hypoglycemia, elevated liver enzyme (ALT), and dyslipidemia (high triglycerides, high LDL). Other parameters are within normal limits. Recommend clinical correlation for possible chronic kidney disease, metabolic disturbance, and cardiovascular risk assessment.
